Maybe you‚Äôve heard about my Mac Cares Challenge to write 100 letters to the residents from Aperion Estates (assisted living facility on Grissom ARB), and I hope you have! In case you need information on this, I am attaching it again to this post. My goal is 100 letters and we‚Äôre about halfway there as of last Friday.

There is a SECOND OPPORTUNITY to show these members of our community that you care about them and wish them well! Remember, they‚Äôve had NO VISITORS for weeks now! On Friday, May 8, there will be a drive-by parade at 2pm. If you‚Äôd like to join them, be in line by 1:45 pm. You could use a karaoke machine and sing as you drive by slowly and wave. You could ride your bike, unicycle, hoverboard, etc! Maybe juggle as you walk by? The Sky is the limit!

Please consider being part of this parade to show them you haven‚Äôt forgotten them and to bring them a smile!

post_text: The choir members who were available today had the privilege of singing some of Mr. Kent Workman‚Äôs favorite songs in his celebration of life ceremony today. The ceremony was so nice, and I personally appreciated past choir/theatre student, Payton Whybrew, contributing a beautiful performance of ‚ÄúI Can Only Imagine.‚Äù I was able to snag a few pictures and videos. Thanks again to all those who attended and helped honor someone who gave most of his life to Maconaquah and Miami County.

post_text: We are excited to announce that our Fall Musical for 2019 is Grease: School Edition! Students in grades 6 - 12 are welcome to audition. Auditions for MMS students will be held in the Middle School choir room on Monday, August 5, 2019, from 3:30 p.m. to 5:00 p.m. Auditions for MHS students will be held in the High School choir room on Tuesday, August 6, 2019, from 3:30 p.m. to 5:00 p.m. If call-backs are needed, they will be held at the MHS choir room on Thursday, August 8,2019. The cast list will be posted on Friday, August 9, 2019, with the first rehearsal being on Saturday, August 10, 2019, from 10:00 a.m. to 11:30 a.m. (you may have additional rehearsal time on August 9th depending on your role).

post_text:
Auditions for 2019-20 Counterpoints and Next Level will be in the high school choir room after school 3:30-4:30 on April 3 and 4. Students in grades 8-11 right now are all invited. There is a packet with permission slip that is required to be turned in. If you need a copy or just want the details, email baileym@maconaquah.k12.in.us.

Counterpoints is a group of male and female voices that sing and dance. This group has been around for a long time and has a tradition of excellence.

Next Level is a group of treble voices who sing and dance. The group debuted about 15 years ago but was dropped several years ago until this current school year. I was able to bring it back as an after school only group. Next year, we have school board approval to have Next Level as a class!! I am over-the-moon excited to have it return. Just in a few short months, the group has made leaps and bounds in improvement.

Again, current 8-11 grade students, I hope to see you there!!!!!

post_text: This weekend only!!! February 22 & 23 at 7:00 pm you can see TWO plays for the price of one! "Stressed" (directed by Michelle Bailey & Michael Sommers) is a one act about teenage life - with both comedy and drama. "Murder by Indecision" (directed by Ann Hileman and her student teacher Kate Scott) is a short full length murder mystery comedy. Advance sale tickets now available for $5.00. Tickets at the door for adults will be $7.00. Twelve and under will pay $5.00 either in advance or at the door. Make plans now to come to the high school to forget about this weather!

post_text: Well. The weather sure is causing problems for this cast and crew. I would like to tell you we were still doing the free performance today at 4 pm, but I can't. You are invited to come to Indy on Saturday at 1:30, but if you do, you may be stuck there for several days. I am not sure yet when we will be packing up the trailer with the set and all - maybe tonight, maybe tomorrow morning. Just don't plan on coming to Maconaquah see the show today at 4 pm.

post_text:
Audition information is now available for our next musical in the fall!! We want to get it out to you soon because the auditions are May 22, 2018 in the HS Choir Room after school until 5 PM for grades 6-11. Grades 3-5 will be auditioned in the fall on August 3 from 3:30-4:30 at Mac El.

There is a $20 musical fee due at auditions. If you are not cast, the fee will be returned. Checks can be written to MHS. More info will be available once we announce the show title.

We will announce the title of the musical for the fall on Friday, May 18 at the Choir/Theatre awards ceremony. The ceremony begins at 6 PM. Any student who has been a part of a musical, play, or in the choir program at MHS is encouraged and invited to attend!
